5-11:They are not reliable to compare the effectiveness of a system on different topics, relative to the other systems .
5-12:If, for example, AP(s1, t1) > AP(s1, t2), can we infer that s1 is a good system (i.e., has a good performance) on t1 and a bad system on t2? The answer is no: t1 might be an easy topic (with high AAP) and t2 a difficult one (low AAP) .
